one investor may see a P-E of 16 -- close to the current level -- are frightfully high while another investor will read the same number as offering more opportunity than risk.  In exploring P-E ratios, the place to start is what we would like to know: will the market go up? \r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWith a little data, one can attempt a non-scientific look at what P-E ratios might suggest.','',443,'https://dev.indexologyblog.com/2013/06/11/443-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0);
