0 next summer, you don’t wait  to sell it.  You sell it now and all that selling makes it worth 90 right now. This is what happened.  Rather than complaining about the fickle Fed, remember their job is worry about what could go wrong, lean against the wind and act as “the chaperone who has ordered the punch bowl removed when the party was really warming up.” (The quote is from William McC. Martin, Fed chairman in the 1950s and 1960s, credit to the <a href=\"http://conversableeconomist.blogspot.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Conversable Economist blog</a> for the citation and a copy of the speech.)\r\n\r\nScorecard:\r\n\r\nS&amp;P 500 down 4.6% and DJIA down 4.3% from the close on Tuesday 6/18 to the close on Monday 6/24. 10 year Treasury note yield rose 38 bp or 17% over same time period.','',714,'https://dev.indexologyblog.com/2013/06/24/714-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0);
