t +0.92%.\r\n\r\nThe FOMC meeting took its toll on investment grade credit as well.  June 19 and 20 showed the two worst daily returns of -0.72% and -0.93%, respectively for the <a href=\"http://us.spindices.com/indices/fixed-income/sp-us-issued-investment-grade-corporate-bond-index\"><b>S&amp;P U.S. Issued Investment Grade Corporate Bond Index</b></a><b>.  </b>The current month-to-date return of -2.71% will be the largest monthly loss since October of 2008’s -5.38%.\r\n\r\n <img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-746\" alt=\"Bond Yield Summary\" src=\"https://dev.indexologyblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Blog-Post-20130628-June.jpg\" width=\"769\" height=\"638\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','',744,'https://dev.indexologyblog.com/2013/06/28/744-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0);
