, and yield-sensitive strategies like the S&amp;P 500 Value or the Dow Jones US Select Dividend Indices outperformed broad market gauges.  <strong>Volatility was the month\'s biggest winner</strong>, as the S&amp;P 500 VIX Short-Term Futures Index gained +7.26%.  Volatility\'s performance also benefited the S&amp;P 500 Dynamic VEQTOR Index, which allocates between stocks and vol, and rose +0.42% in June.','',695,'https://dev.indexologyblog.com/2013/06/30/695-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0);
