n in backwardation with 3 months occurring in 2011, 5 months in 2012 and 2 in 2013 (May and June).</span>\r\n\r\nWhat does it mean? If <span style=\"font-size: 1rem;line-height: 1.714285714\">there is a shift in environment going forward towards a world driven by expansion of demand, then backwardation may be more likely with more frequent cycle switching. If </span><span style=\"line-height: 1.714285714;font-size: 1rem\">this is the case, then like in 2012, </span>the fixed forward indices like the S&amp;P GSCI 3-Month Forward may underperform the S&amp;P GSCI, which holds the nearby most liquid contracts, or more dynamic indices like the S&amp;P GSCI Dynamic Roll and the newly launched S&amp;P GSCI Roll Weight Select.','',808,'https://dev.indexologyblog.com/2013/07/08/808-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0);
