xcess return and price return versions of the  <a href=\"http://us.spindices.com/index-family/commodities/sp-gsci\" target=\"_blank\">S&amp;P GSCI</a>), appeared in 5 months in 2012 an has now persisted since May 2013.\r\n\r\nThere are a number of factors that are associated with <a href=\"http://www.zerohedge.com/article/coming-new-world-order-revolution-how-things-will-change-next-20-years-kondratieff-cycle-per\" target=\"_blank\">characteristics of world growth</a> driven by expansion of demand that are shifting from world growth driven by expansion of supply.  These factors are becoming more apparent since last year and they may drive the frequency and magnitude of cycles higher that may increase the frequency of switching between contango and backwardation.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user5/imageroot/draghi/NWO%201.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1045\" alt=\"New World\" src=\"https://dev.indexologyblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/New-World.jpg\" width=\"1065\" height=\"513\" /></a>\r\n\r\nFrom this shift, the inventories are lower so commodities have been more sensitive to supply shocks than they have been in the past as evidenced by the moves in <a title=\"THE Golden Question?\" href=\"https://dev.indexologyblog.com/2013/07/25/the-golden-question/\" target=\"_blank\">gold</a>, <a title=\"Where’s the beef?\" href=\"https://dev.indexologyblog.com/2013/07/18/wheres-the-beef/\" target=\"_blank\">livestock</a>, and <a title=\"Paying Too Much at the Pump?!\" href=\"https://dev.indexologyblog.com/2013/08/01/paying-too-much-at-the-pump/\" target=\"_blank\">energy</a>. This is important since div','',1038,'https://dev.indexologyblog.com/2013/08/06/1038-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0);
